Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a large #bowl{}, toss @cauliflower florets{20%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Transfer to a #baking sheet{} and roast in oven until golden brown, about ~{25%minutes}.

> Don't worry if a few crumbs fall off.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{2}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add onions and cook until softened, about ~{4-5%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon} and reduce heat to low. Cook until very soft, about ~{10%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from pan and set aside.

Shape @ground beef{16%ounce} into four evenly-sized patties with your hands. Season with @dried oregano{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Carefully wipe out pan you cooked onions in with a #paper towel{}, then heat a drizzle of oil in pan over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, about ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Combine @mayonnaise{2%jar} and garlic in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Split @brioche buns{4} in half, place on another baking sheet, and toast in oven until golden brown, about ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Start with a pinch of garlic, then go up from there for the aioli.

Spread garlic aioli on buns and top each with a burger and onions. Serve with cauliflower on the side.